### Life Vault API Testing Guide
### Use with REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = your-jwt-token-here

### ==================== AUTHENTICATION ====================

### 1. Send OTP for Signup
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 2. Verify OTP and Create Account
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "otp": "123456",
  "name": "Test User",
  "age": 25,
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "password": "TestPass123!"
}

### 3. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!"
}

### 4. Forgot Password - Send OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 5. Reset Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "otp": "123456",
  "newPassword": "NewPass123!"
}

### ==================== PRESENT VAULT ====================

### 6. Get Present Vault Slots
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/vaults/present/slots
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Create Slot in Present Vault
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/vaults/present/slots
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "slotName": "Birthday Party"
}

### 8. Add Text to Slot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/slots/{slotId}/text
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Had an amazing birthday celebration with friends!"
}

### 9. Schedule Slot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/slots/{slotId}/schedule
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "recipientEmail": "recipient@example.com",
  "scheduledDate": "2026-03-10T10:00:00Z",
  "vaultType": "present"
}

### ==================== FUTURE VAULT ====================

### 10. Get Future Vault Slots
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/vaults/future/slots
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Create Slot in Future Vault
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/vaults/future/slots
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "slotName": "Anniversary"
}

### ==================== DEATH VAULT ====================

### 12. Get Death Vault Slots
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/vaults/death/slots
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 13. Add Recipient to Death Vault Slot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/slots/{slotId}/schedule
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "recipientEmail": "mom@example.com",
  "scheduledDate": "2026-11-10T10:00:00Z",
  "vaultType": "death"
}

### ==================== SHARED VAULT ====================

### 14. View Shared Slot
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/shared-vault/{accessToken}

### ==================== INACTIVITY ====================

### 15. Confirm Alive
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/confirm-alive/{confirmationToken}

### ==================== SLOT OPERATIONS ====================

### 16. Delete Slot
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/slots/{slotId}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vaultType": "present"
}

### 17. Get Slot Details
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/slots/{slotId}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 18. Create Nested Slot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/slots/{parentSlotId}/nested
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "slotName": "Dad on a trip"
}

### ==================== NOTES ====================
### 
### 1. Replace {slotId}, {accessToken}, {confirmationToken} with actual values
### 2. Replace {{token}} with your JWT token from login response
### 3. Check MongoDB to verify data is being stored correctly
### 4. Use browser DevTools (F12) to check network requests
### 5. Check email inbox for OTP codes (may be in spam folder)
